body: - [**CHANGED**]: Deprecate `try` functions in favor of `Result.init(attempt:)` (#251)
- [**CHANGED**]: Deprecate `ErrorProtocolConvertible` in favor of `ErrorConvertible` (#230)
- [**FIXED**]: Improve `AnyError` support in `Result.init(attempt:)` (#224)
- [**FIXED**]: Swift 3.1 compatibility issue on Linux (#212, #214)

- [**NEW**]: Add `ResultProtocol.bimap(success:failure:)` method (#116, #205)
- [**NEW**]: Add `ResultProtocol.fanout(_:)` as an alternative to `&&&` operator (#204)
- [**NEW**]: Add `LocalizedError` conformance to `AnyError` on Darwin platforms (#210)
- [**CHANGED**]: Deprecate `>>-` and `&&&` operators (#206)

- [**NEW**]: Add `Equatable` conformance to `NoError` (#200, #201)
- [**NEW**]: Add type-erased `AnyError` for generic contexts. `materialize` overload for `AnyError` is also added (#198)
- [**CHANGED**]: `materialize` for `NSError` is now deprecated in favor of the overload for `AnyError` (#198)

- [**CHANGED**]: Drop Swift 2.x support
- [**CHANGED**]: Swift 3 API Design Guidelines
- [**CHANGED**]: Support for Swift 3.0

API changes from 2.x:
- `Result`
  - `.Success` to `.success`
  - `.Failure` to `.failure`
- `ResultType` to `ResultProtocol`
  - `recoverWith(_:)` to `recover(with:)`
- `ResultErrorType` to `Swift.Error`
- `ErrorTypeConvertible` to `ErrorProtocolConvertible`
  - `errorFromErrorType_:)` to `error(from:)`

name: 2.1.1: Results, Not Excuses
body:

name: 2.1.0: Future Results
body:
- [**CHANGED**]: `recover`, `recoverWith`, `==`, `!=`, `??`, and `>>-` are now defined in terms of `ResultType`
- [**CHANGED**]: `ConvertibleType` was removed from `ErrorTypeConvertible`
- [**CHANGED**]: Swift 3 support has been updated to the 2016-05-31 snapshot
- [**NEW**]: Unused results will now trigger a warning

name: 1.0.2: A Swift Result
body:

name: 1.0.1: A New Beginning
body:

name: 1.0: Real Results
body:
:tada: 1.0! :tada: 

This has been in beta for a _while_. Thanks to everyone who helped improve it and push it forward during that time.

Summary of changes since the 0.4 series of releases (See the 0.5 and 0.6 series of beta releases for more detailed info):
- [**NEW**]: Swift 2.0 support
- [**NEW**]: Translate to and from Swift 2 functions using `throw`
- [**NEW**]: `tvOS` support
- [**CHANGED**]: Removed dependency on Box

name: 0.6.0 Beta 6: Apple TV, take three
body:
- **[fixed]** Added Apple TV deployment target to the podspec
- **[fixed]** Added second `materialize` without `@autoclosure` to be compatible with trailing closure syntax

name: 0.6 Beta 5: remember that TV thing?
body: - **[new]** Apple TV scheme is available again (_note: it requires `Xcode 7.1`_)

name: 0.4.5: Frozen Box
body: - **[fixed]** Add a version constraint to `Box` dependency for compatibility with Swift 1.2.

name: 0.6 Beta 4: Bitcode Build
body: Updated the build settings so that Result can be built with Carthage for targets that require bitcode.

name: 0.6 Beta 3: Just kidding about that TV thing
body: Removed the `tvOS` scheme from the project in order to fix builds with Carthage and Xcode 7. We'll re-add this with Xcode 7.1.

name: 0.6 Beta 2: Materialize Build
body:
- **[new]** free `materialize` function that takes a function of the type `() throws -> T` and returns `Result<T, NSError>`
- **[new]** tvOS Support
- **[Fixed]**  Explicitly set code signing to work around bugs in `xcodebuild`

name: 0.6: Swift 2 beta
body:
- **[new]** A `ResultType` protocol that can be used in protocol extension & generics constraints. `Result` implements `ResultType`.
- **[new]** Construct a result with a throwing closure using `init(@autoclosure _ f: () throws -> T)`
- **[new]** Deconstruct a result into a value or a Swift 2 `ErrorType` using `dematerialize()`

name: 0.5: Swift 2 Beta
body: - **[improved]** Removes `Box` dependency because Swift 2 supports multi-payload enums.

name: 0.4.3: @autoclobber
body: - **[fixed]** non-short-circuiting evaluation of `recover` and `recoverWith`’s operands.

name: 0.4.2: Discover Recover
body: - **[new]** `recover` and `recoverWith` as synonyms for `??`. (Thanks, @nvh!)

name: 0.4.1: Oh Ess Ex
body: - **[fixed]** #21 and #25, caused by the OS X targets for Result and Box supporting i386 as a valid architecture.

name: 0.4: Once More Unto The Box
body:
- **[new]** `Result` is once again an `enum` and can be pattern matched over.
- **[new]** We depend upon [`Box`](https://github.com/robrix/Box) again so that it can used as a shared dependency without introducing ambiguity.

name: 0.3.2: How Did That Even Work?
body: - **[fixed]** The tests no longer depend on a framework which Xcode found by :sparkles: magic :sparkles:.

name: 0.3.1: Now with Actually Builds™!
body: - **[fixed]** building for iOS, :tophat: @jcavar

name: 0.3: I Got 99 Problems but a Dependency Ain’t One
body: - **[improved]** Result is standalone (it has no dependencies of its own)

name: 0.2: Only App Extensions Can Do This
body: - **[new]** App extension support, c/o @NachoSoto!
Initial release.
